The article discusses President Obama's commitment to breaking down barriers to women's economic and political participation. The Obama Administration has taken various steps to empower women and girls both domestically and internationally. Some of these steps include signing the Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Act, ensuring affordable and accessible healthcare for women, creating jobs and economic security for women, preventing violence against women, integrating women into U.S. foreign policy, promoting women as central to U.S. development efforts, advancing women's economic participation, and advancing efforts on women's political participation. President Obama challenged other heads of state to announce steps their governments will take to ensure women's full and equal participation in their countries' economic and political spheres. The White House Council on Women and Girls and National Security Staff will coordinate the ongoing efforts to support women's empowerment.